cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.IT, cs.NI

The paper proposes a solution for adaptive multiview video streaming, which involves video encoding, transmission, and client-side decoding. Therefore, it can be categorized under multiple sub-categories of computer science. 

cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with video streaming, which is a multimedia application. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper involves the use of camera views, which are related to computer vision. 

cs.GR (Graphics): The paper deals with the transmission of multiple views, which can be considered as a graphics problem. 

cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper formulates an optimization problem for the selection of views subsets and their encoding rates, which is related to information theory. 

cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with video streaming over the network, which is related to networking and internet architecture.
